properties.Description: The Vessel Sewage No Discharge Zone includes all Washington marine waters east of New Dungeness Lighthouse, at the east end of the Strait of Juan de Fuca, plus fresh waters of Lake Washington, Lake Union, and the waters that connect them to Puget Sound.
properties.NDZLaw: WAC 173-228 bans vessel sewage discharges, whether treated or not, in the No Discharge Zone. It became effective May 10, 2018.
